        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are 12 E tiles in a standard English Scrabble game, making E the most common letter. Each E tile is worth 1 point. With 12 out of 100 total tiles being E, you have a 12% chance of drawing an E on any single draw from a full bag." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many blank tiles are in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are exactly 2 blank tiles in a standard Scrabble game. Blank tiles are worth 0 points but can represent any letter. They are the most strategically valuable tiles because they enable bingos (using all 7 tiles for a 50-point bonus) by filling in whatever letter you need." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
