        Every Scrabble game starts with 100 tiles in the bag — 98 letters and 2 blanks. Knowing the exact distribution gives you a strategic advantage: you can track which tiles remain, estimate what your opponent holds, and make better decisions about exchanging or holding tiles. This complete guide covers every tile count, point value, and the tile tracking strategy that tournament players use.
