      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Most Common vs Rarest Tiles</h2>

      <p>Understanding tile frequency helps you predict what is likely still in the bag and what your opponent might be holding. The most common tiles are low-value vowels and consonants, while the rarest are high-value power tiles.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📊 Most Common (6+ tiles)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E: 12 tiles · A: 9 tiles · I: 9 tiles · O: 8 tiles · N: 6 tiles · R: 6 tiles · T: 6 tiles. These 7 letters make up 56 of 100 tiles (56%).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💎 Rarest (1 tile only)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q: 1 tile (10pts) · Z: 1 tile (10pts) · X: 1 tile (8pts) · J: 1 tile (8pts) · K: 1 tile (5pts). Once played, these are gone for the rest of the game.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📈 Medium Frequency (2-4 tiles)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">D: 4 tiles · S: 4 tiles · U: 4 tiles · L: 4 tiles · G: 3 tiles · B/C/F/H/M/P/V/W/Y: 2 tiles each.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ Strategic S Tiles</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Only 4 S tiles exist. Each is worth just 1 point but can pluralize any word on the board — often scoring 20+ points by hooking onto existing words. Never waste an S for less than 10 extra points.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Tile Tracking: What Is Left in the Bag?</h2>

      <p>Tile tracking is the practice of monitoring which tiles have been played so you know what remains in the bag. Tournament players do this on a tracking sheet, crossing off letters as they appear on the board.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Why Track Tiles?</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">In the endgame (when the bag is empty), tile tracking tells you <span class="text-white font-medium">exactly</span> what your opponent holds. This turns Scrabble from a game of probability into a game of perfect information — like chess. You can block their best plays and set up unstoppable moves.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Start simple:</span> Track only the power tiles first (Q, Z, X, J, blanks, S tiles). As you get comfortable, expand to tracking all consonants, then vowels.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pre-printed sheets:</span> Use a tracking sheet with all 100 tiles listed. Cross off tiles as they appear on the board. Most tournament players use a columnar format sorted by letter.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Endgame power:</span> When the bag is empty and you know all remaining tiles, you can calculate your opponent's exact rack. This lets you play defense (blocking) or offense (setting up unblockable plays).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Probability decisions:</span> Midgame, knowing 8 of 12 E tiles are played means E is scarce — avoid words requiring E. Knowing the blank is still out means a bingo could appear any turn.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Implications of the Distribution</h2>

      <p>The tile distribution is not random — it reflects English letter frequency. This has direct strategic implications for how you play.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Vowel Balance</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">42 of 98 letter tiles are vowels (43%). Ideal rack has 2-3 vowels. More than 4 vowels = consider exchanging. Fewer than 2 = consonant-heavy, look for short plays.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Vowel Dumps</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">If stuck with 5+ vowels, play vowel-heavy words: AIOLI, ADIEU, AUDIO, OUIJA, AWEIGH. These dump excess vowels while scoring decent points.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

